<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="After3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">After,</orth> conj. subsequently to the time when: <cit><quote>a. they closed in earnest, they parted in jest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 5, 13</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 261</bibl> etc. Followed by a present: <cit><quote>a. my flame lacks oil,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls I, 2, 59</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. he scores,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.253" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 253</bibl></cit>. <emph>A. that,</emph> see <emph>That.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>